<!-- ── SECTION 8: WEST INDIA ── -->
<section id="west">
  <div class="sec-eyebrow">Section 8 — West India</div>
  <div class="sec-title">Gujarat &amp; Maharashtra Communities</div>
  <p class="sec-intro">
    West India is a genetic transition zone between the high-Steppe northwest and the low-Steppe south. Gujarat communities preserve some of the most extreme founder effects documented globally (Parsis, certain Brahmin groups). Maharashtra shows a gradient from northwestern-type ancestry in upper castes to more AASI-heavy ancestry in tribal communities. <span class="ref-tag">BAS16</span><span class="ref-tag">NAR19</span>
  </p>

